metadata.name: Traversal #7
metadata.description:
Traversal is the marriage of two simple geometric ideas: a set of somewhat unruly, intersecting diagonal shapes, and a minimally reduced corner perspective that gives them depth.

The depicted bodies are entirely feasible as a 3D scene, and yet this composition is all about illusion. The hatch fill creates a perception of light. The dithering on the faces produces a sense of material texture. The squiggly lines imitate freehand drawing. The spatial perspective itself is achieved through a purely two-dimensional algorithm of polygon intersections and line hiding.

The original medium of my compositions is the pen plotter, and Traversal is no exception. It is entirely vector-based, and can be plotted directly. I use Paper.js to render it on-screen and as SVG.

~

To generate and download a plottable SVG file, press `S`. Please be patient; this process can take a while. The SVG can be plotted on an A5 paper. It contains two layers visible in Inkscape, so you can plot the light grey sketch lines with a different pen, or omit them altogether.

metadata.name: Lost Twins #47
metadata.description:
Individually, the mints of this token are very simple. Each mint generates half of two cube forms, and each half is assigned random hues (in multiples of 10, from 0 to 360). Collectively as a project, this token challenges the approach of looking for "rarities" in a new way. How the cubes are rendered leaves the possibility for multiple mints to potentially join up on the sides with colors that perfect match each other. Will you find your lost twin?

Made in p5js
Created November 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Plottable Storm #93
metadata.description:
Plottable Storm is a flow field simulating fountain pen ink drawing on paper on its digital form. 10 inks, many rarity features varying noise, size and color positioning. Having only one color is rare.
The digital NFTs can be used to perform a physical action: @greweb plotting on demand a fountain pen plot for those who also want physical originals. Full article: https://greweb.me/2021/11/plottable-storm

Digital and Physical art, hybrid and decoupled:
- The art is made as a regular digital NFT on Tezos blockchain â€“ its digital form rendered with WebGL shaders.
- Token to the physical world: owning each NFT confer the power to request the related physical plot â€“ See https://greweb.me/plots/nft

Tip: right click or Drag&Drop the canvas will get you the plottable SVG.
